The paper discusses improvements to the Neural GPU architecture for algorithm learning, which is a problem in artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions deep learning methods, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), making these sub-categories likely as well. Additionally, the paper discusses techniques for improving generalization, which is a common problem in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of gates, which are commonly used in neural networks for memory management, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
